jHqPntk3K1A.description:
With TikTok making beauty products go viral every other day, it seems that more and more products are being released in the hope of becoming the next big thing. From the NYX Fat Oil Lip Drip vegan lip oil, a hydrating lip oil, to the Half Magic Cheek Fluff, a pillowy cream to powder blush, we rounded up some of the most-hyped products from February to test out for ourselves.

transcript_raw.text: There are so many new beauty releases
happening all the time,

so we gathered some of
the most-hyped products
to test for ourselves.
I'm a lip-oil freak,

so I was dying to try out
these NYX Fat Oil Lip Drips.
I bought so many.

They have the huge doe-foot
applicator that I love
and a very subtle fruity scent.

This isn't a perfect dupe
for the Dior lip oil.
The formula is slightly thinner,
and the brush doesn't pick up
and apply the product as smoothly,

but these definitely have
more of a color payoff.
I do think this is the best lip oil
I've tried from the drugstore for sure.

It feels so comfortable
and hydrating on the lips,
and I love the range of colors they have.

I haven't tried a powder
foundation in a minute.
This is the Maybelline Super Stay
hybrid powder-foundation.
I just used the little sponge
that came with the powder to apply it

all over my already
moisturized and primed face.

This powder is meant to give
medium to full coverage.
I feel like it's more full coverage,
but it doesn't look cakey to me.
I didn't even use concealer with this

because I felt like the
coverage it gave me was enough.
I noticed that it did exaggerate
the dryness around my nose a bit,

but some setting spray helped
it all melt into the skin
and not look so dry.

My other products blended
on top of this just fine,
and it feels super weightless on the skin,
and I noticed that I wasn't as oily
at the end of the day.
About-face released these
Cherry Pick lip color butters,
and I am in love with these.

This kind of lipstick formula
is so popular right now,
but this one is 100% my favorite.

They apply like butter,
as the name suggests.
Just so creamy and moisturizing.
It feels like a slippy lip balm,

but you still get a
really nice color payoff,
and they kind of smell like peaches to me,
but not in a gross, super-artificial way.
I highly recommend these.
This is the Half Magic Cheek Fluff.
I love that name because
it describes this formula perfectly.

It's this supersoft,
fluffy, putty-like blush
that is so buildable.
I genuinely think this blush is foolproof.
Like, you can't apply too much.

I'm typically very
heavy-handed with my makeup,

but this applied like
a soft flush of color.
It looks kind of blurring on the cheeks,
which I really liked.
It also comes in this compostable
and recyclable packaging,
which is so great to see.

We have another transfer-proof
lipstick to test out.

This is the Revlon ColorStay
Suede Ink lipstick.

This really does feel
like suede on the lips.

It's a very soft and
comfortable matte finish
that doesn't feel drying at all.
For the most part
they had really good color payoff,
except this brighter red-orange.
This one was actually pretty patchy,
so just a warning in case

you were interested in
the brighter shades.
I did a little kiss test on my hand,
and they actually are transfer-proof.

This is my first time ever
trying Oden's Eye cosmetics.

They released these
Jewel Shine eyeshadows,
and I had to test them out.
Ignore that blue shade. It came damaged,
but I still wanted to swatch it anyway.
There are two formulas with these,
the multichromes and the shimmers.
The multichromes are more expensive.
These formulas are just so buttery smooth.
They have beautiful glitter in them
that doesn't feel chunky,

and it doesn't give
you fallout everywhere.

They look so pretty
and shifty on the eyes,
and they have, like, a billion colors.
It was so hard to choose.
I really enjoyed using these,

and I want to try more Oden's
Eye products in the future.
This product caught my eye one day
when I was just scrolling through Ulta.
This is the Pacifica Kind Glaze
Dewy Glow Layer face primer.

That name reeled me in,
and I just had to try it.

I was kind of expecting
it to be clear and oily,

but it's more like a creamy,
slightly pigmented gel.

It does add a really
natural glow to the skin.
Like, it's not metallic-looking.
I used my go-to foundation on top,
and I think this is a really nice primer.
My foundation looked really smooth,

and I could see that subtle
glow peeking through.
16 bucks is a lot for the drugstore,
but I really liked this.

This is the Sacheu
Beauty lip liner Stay-N.

It's a peel-off lip liner
that leaves a stain behind.

This is so much like
that peel-off lipstick
I tested a while back.
You have to leave this on for 20 minutes,
which I thought was a little nuts.
That's so much time.
The first time I did it,
the stain was just kind of noticeable.
I used the nude shade,
but it looked way more pink than nude.

I did it again to see if I
could make it more pigmented,
and it kind of worked.
I could definitely see it more,
but I feel like it just looked patchy.
I do have a pigmented lip line,

so maybe that's why it's
not looking great on me.
I feel like this is a good idea
but not a great execution.

Haus Labs just released
this Color Fuse blush.
These colors are just delicious.
I'm so in love with them.
The Haus Labs powder formulas
are some of the best I've ever tried.
This literally just melts into the skin.
It looks so smooth on the cheeks,

and you can build up
the color really easily.
Like, you can make these look as vibrant
as they look in the pan.
These are pricey,

but I think a talc-free
formula this good is worth it.

This is the MAC lash dry
shampoo mascara refresher,

and it's supposed to soften
your existing mascara

so your mascara is
refreshed but not clumpy.
I don't know if that made any sense,
but let's talk about it.
So, the first time I tried it,

I applied it over my mascara
that was a few hours old,

and it wasn't softening
the mascara at all.

Then I realized this can't be
used over waterproof mascara.

So I tried it again
over my regular mascara,
and it worked so much better.

This is one of those
products though that's, like,
yeah, it works, but at the same time,
do I really need this? Probably not.

Danessa Myricks released
these Yummy skin-blurring
balm powder flushed blushes.
I think this is the same formula
as the balm powder, just in blush form.
These are so pigmented,

but in the you-need-to-be-careful
kind of way.
Apply too much, and you will regret it.
My preferred way to apply
was to warm some up on the back of my hand
and slowly build it up with a brush
so I have more control.
These are really smooth and blurring.
They have this kind of soft-matte finish
that looks really pretty.
Alissa Ashley influenced me to buy

the Sephora Microsmooth
face powder years ago,
and I stopped using it for some reason,
but I don't know why,
because this is an amazing product.
It is the smoothest, silkiest powder
that you can do so much with.
It's described as a powder foundation,
but you can also use this to set makeup,
to bronze, or to highlight.

I just used this as an
all-over finishing powder,

and it immediately gives
you this soft-focus finish.
It applies so beautifully

without making your
skin look cakey and dry.

I am definitely obsessed
with this once again.
This is the KVD Good Apple full-coverage
transfer-proof serum foundation.
I have to address this immediately:

This is, like, four shades
too light for me, but we move.
I still wanted to test the formula.
This has pretty full coverage,

but not to the point
where it looks unnatural,
if that makes sense.

It dried down very quickly
and had a more matte finish

than I was expecting with
the word "serum" in the name.
It looked OK over my more textured areas.
It didn't look cakey,
and it felt lightweight on my skin.
It's a very OK foundation.
Didn't love it, didn't hate it,
I just know that $42 is a lot for it.

ColourPop released these
adorable highlighters
that I had to purchase because ... hearts.

These are more subtle
than I was expecting.
I did have to build them up a bit,

but they didn't get chunky
or too metallic-looking.
They build up really nicely.

I was mostly excited to
try out this lavender one
because I never wear color highlighter.
The purply color was pretty obvious,
but it actually looked so cute.

This is the Wet n Wild
5-in-1 essence primer liquid.

So you shake this really well,
then apply it to the face.
You have to let it sit for a minute
before you apply your makeup.

I actually think this gave
me a really nice base.

My skin looked a bit
smoother, it looked glowy,
and it had a slight tackiness to it.
I tend to like a tacky primer.

All of my makeup applied
really well on top of this,

and I didn't get oilier than
normal throughout the day.
This has a lot of mixed reviews,
but I liked this primer.

These are the Charlotte Tilbury
matte beauty blush wands.

People have been using her
highlighter wands as blush,
but this is the first actual blush wand.
These have amazing color payoff.
A little goes a really long way,
but you want to move fast with these.
They do dry down a bit quickly.
But these are so pretty,

and they blend out really
well over other products.
I love these.

Another day, another
glossy lipstick to try out.

This is the Flower Beauty
plump up gloss stick.

The formula is thinner
than I was expecting,

just based on other similar
lip products I've tried.
It doesn't really plump much.
You just get a slight tingling feeling.

This feels so nice and
hydrating on the lips,

but it's more like a lip
balm than a lip gloss.

and just like the texture and how your skin feels,
then I can definitely recommend Pyunkang Yul's products to you.
There is this Moisture Cream from Pyunkang
Yul, only it is formulated in a relatively basic way.
It doesn't have as many extras as this cream, but the product
is completely fragrance-free, unlike the one from Glow Recipe.

it's moisturizing and it's very light on the skin
and you can easily layer other products on top of it.

rather a moisturizing effect.

that just came out, so this newer one, the Moisturizing
Barrier Cream, is also very, very similar

and the texture, but don't like this perfume that much,
then you should definitely take a look at the moisturizers from Pyunkang Yul.

having
to try different techniques that I personally don't like

I'll wash my face off afterwards, but other than that it's just
not a foundation
that I like to use on a daily basis because it is looks ugly on my skin.
An alternative that costs a lot less and that
I use much, much more regularly, especially when I use foundation.
And now I very, very rarely use foundation.
And then I also want to have a foundation that I can rely on,
that I can tolerate and that also looks good on my skin.
And that's where I love to use the Hypoallergenic
Longwear Hydrating Balm Foundation.
I take a pump of this, apply it to my face
and have a light coverage exactly where I need it.
It doesn't sit strangely on my skin, I tolerate it wonderfully
and it doesn't cost 42 €.

qJbP4sk7XgE.title: Charlotte Tilbury Viral Makeup
qJbP4sk7XgE.description:
Charlotte Tilbury New Matte Blush Wand Full Details:  http://bit.ly/3kSVM0w 
Full Face of Charlotte Tilbury viral makeup, best sellers and new releases. Hollywood Flawless Filter has to be one of the most hyped makeup products from Charlotte Tilbury. This face base filter is most used as a primer before foundation all over the face. Personally, I only like to apply Hollywood Flawless Filter on the high points of my face to highlight those features. A new single eyeshadow called Pillow Talk Hypnotizing Pop Shot Eyeshadow in shade Violet is stunning and so easy to wear on its own to make your eyes pop. I love the way the violet shade brings out my green eyes. 

One of the biggest makeup launches by Charlotte Tilbury is Pillow Talk. Pillow talk has so many makeup products under the line from mascara, eyeshadow, highlighter, lipstick, lip liner and so much more. 

Another Charlotte Tilbury makeup product that is being duped is the famous Hollywood Contour Wand. It’s an award winning liquid contour wand that is really easy to use for everyday to get the perfect contour. The newest makeup release from Charlotte Tilbury is the Matte Beauty Blush Wand. There are four shades to chose from that provide a soft wash of color with a matte finish. To set my makeup, I use Charlotte Tilbury Airbrush Flawless Finish. This pressed powder is really finely milled and looks flawless on the skin while setting the makeup in place. 

Personally, I think Charlotte Tilbury eyebrow products are overlooked. Her Brow Cheat eyebrow pencil paired with the tinted Legendary Brows is a match made in heaven. Brow cheat pencil has a creamy formula that allows to draw brow hair like strokes, while Legendary Brow tinted gel sets my brows for an all day wear. 

Pillow Talk is iconic in Charlotte Tilbury lip formulas from lip liners to lipsticks. My personal favorite shades from lip liners are Pillow Talk 2 and Icon Nude. If you’re looking for a matte lipstick with comfortable wear throughout the day, check out Charlotte Tilbury Matte Revolution lipstick collection. The iconic Pillow Talk lipstick is a beautiful nude-pink with a soft matte finish. Some of my other favorite lipstick formulas include Hot Lips and Hot Lips 2. Both lipstick formulas have a satin finish.

So if you picked a too intense color like wicked apple, you can put it on your finger and dab over your lips and it will look super natural but more flustered. 10/10 product

Once you figure out what application technique works best for you, the eyeshadow really pays off. And it does last all day heck, even into the next day. When you apply it, keep your eye closed for about 30 seconds or so, that way the shadow will set and not crease when you open and close your eyes. Shadow doesn't even need touch ups.💯

Nico - I'd love to get an update, maybe every few months, of what products you test that go into your daily rotation. There's definitely a big difference between "I liked this once" and "I like this so much I now use it every day."
That red eyeshadow looked so gorgeous on you and I love how you applied it!
Girl the orange lip oil and the red eyeshadow looked SO GOOD and also the haus labs blush? You deadass looked like a pinterest girlie
I love these so much! I look forward to them every month. Would you do a personal recommendations video of all of your favorite products, please?
OMG!! That red eyeshadow look! Have heard nothing but great things about Oden's Eye.  Awesome wrap up as usual. Ur the best reviewer. 🎉🎉
That HalfMagic blush looks so good. There’s a couple items I think I’m gonna try. Thank for another great video💖

So happy Oden's Eye is getting talked about more!! Their eyeshadow palettes are amazing, so much pigment and blend super well, and I have a few of their highlighters which I also love. Can't wait to try some of their singles too!
Watching Nico apply lipstick is like... hypnotic 💋 Man is she is stunning!!
I'm not at all a huge make up wearer, but I absolutely love these videos and the lovely reviewer!! Very soothing while doing my skincare routine hi hi❤❤❤

Those cherry pick lip from About-face are SOOO freaking good. Find a natural color that is close to your lip color and it will just pop. You can choose the coverage too, it’s buildable. So if you picked a too intense color like wicked apple, you can put it on your finger and dab over your lips and it will look super natural but more flustered. 10/10 product

Revlon usually does good lip colors. Maybelline color tattoo eyeshadow has a bunch of nice eyeshadow colors. Once you figure out what application technique works best for you, the eyeshadow really pays off. And it does last all day heck, even into the next day. When you apply it, keep your eye closed for about 30 seconds or so, that way the shadow will set and not crease when you open and close your eyes. Shadow doesn't even need touch ups.💯
I usually poo poo the drugstore stuff but I'm so glad you're reviewing it because you really opened my eyes to new products, a big thank you to you!
I've seen mixed reviews on the Maybelline powder foundation and I've really wanted to try it. Seeing your review has definitely made me want it now. Thanks Hun xx

That red shimmer looked absolutely amazing on you

hehe i follow this channel literally only for these monthly videos and i do not even use makeup so i just- props to youu <33

So if you picked a too intense color like wicked apple, you can put it on your finger and dab over your lips and it will look super natural but more flustered. 10/10 product

Once you figure out what application technique works best for you, the eyeshadow really pays off. And it does last all day heck, even into the next day. When you apply it, keep your eye closed for about 30 seconds or so, that way the shadow will set and not crease when you open and close your eyes. Shadow doesn't even need touch ups.💯

ORn5bRYDaug.title: Physicians Formula Mineral Wear Diamond Last Lip Cream
ORn5bRYDaug.description:
Achieve bold, creamy and nourishing lip color that lasts all day long with Physicians Formula Mineral Wear Diamond Last lip cream! This long-wearing, ultra-creamy, and richly colored lip color delivers weightless saturated color in a single swipe. Say goodbye to touchups because this lip color is one and done: simply swipe on and you’re good to go for the rest of the day. Comfortable and hydrating, this lip color is blended with ethically sourced Lustrous Diamond Dust creates next level brilliant color while a soothing blend of Mineral Water and nourishing Vitamin E provides instant hydration and transforms dull, dehydrated lips, leaving them smooth and soft to the touch.

One-Step Color: Enjoy vibrant color in a single swipe! The included applicator brush applies just the right amount of color to the lips for all-day wear.

Lip-Loving Ingredients: This velvety lip color is blended with real Lustrous Diamond Dust creates next level brilliant color. Add in a soothing blend of Mineral Water and nourishing Vitamin E to provide instant hydration to transform dull, dehydrated lips, leaving them smooth and soft to the touch.

Made For Sensitive Skin: Physicians Formula makeup is specifically formulated with your skin and comfort in mind. That’s why we use high-quality ingredients, leaving you looking and feeling beautiful from the inside out.

Cruelty-Free: All Physicians Formula foundations, eye makeup, lipsticks, and other cosmetics are always cruelty-free and never tested on animals.

This product is: Cruelty Free. Fragrance-Free. Gluten Free. Paraben-Free. Talc Free. Vegan.

SHOP: https://pformu.la/diamond-last-lip
For more information, please visit www.physiciansformula.com

lGxJZ3FD2Ms.title: Simple Daily Makeup Look
lGxJZ3FD2Ms.description:
Hello guy!
In this video, I'll show you my daily go-to makeup look. 
It’s important to make sure our skin stay hydrated and moist, so the makeup can sit beautifully on the skin without looking cakey and dry. 
Hope you guys enjoy this video :)

Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/naomi.natali3/ 

LIST OF PRODUCTS:
1. I'm From - Mugwort Essence
2. iUNIK Beta Glucan Moisturiser
3. Beauty of Joseon Relief Sun Rice Probiotics 
4. Loreal Infallible Resurfacing Primer
5. IT Cosmetics Your Skin But Better CC Cream SPF50
6. IT Cosmetics Bye Bye Undereye Full Coverage Anti-Ageing Waterproof Concealer
7. Australis Eyeshadow Primer
8. Coringco Shabamshabam #04 - Venice Night
9. Bobbi Brown Longwear Gel Eyeliner 
10. Holika Holika Wonder Drawing Skinning Eyebrow
11. Kat Von D Beauty Tattoo Liner Liquid Eyeliner 
12. Makeup Forever Ultra HD Loose Powder
13. Tarte Winter Wonderglam Lux Eye Palette
14. Romand Better Than Cheek #01 Tangerine Chip
15. Bobbi Brown Crushed Lip Color - Blondie Pink
16. MAC Lipstick - Whirl
17. Tarte Lights, Camera, Splashes, 4 in 1 Waterproof Mascara
18. Real Technique Everyday Essentials Brush Sets 

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
BAHASA INDONESIA:

Halo semua!
Ini video makeup tutorial untuk daily makeup look.
Jangan lupa untuk selalu menjaga kelembapkan kulit kalian dengan skincare yang tepat yah, supaya makeup yang melekat diwajah juga terlihat natural dan tidak keliatan kering. 
Semoga video tutorialnya membantu yah! :)

Suite au buzz sur les reseaux sociaux, j'ai voulu voir exactement de mes propres yeux ce qu'était le "fameux" fond de teint Sérum Good Apple de KVD
Ce fond de teint promet un fini naturel ,haute couvrance ,sans transfert, léger comme un sérum. Il doit flouter nos pores, resister à la chaleur et à la transpiration avec sa couvrance modulable. 
Voyons comment ce fond de teint se comporte sur ma peau de 50 ans.

Those cherry pick lip from About-face are SOOO freaking good. Find a natural color that is close to your lip color and it will just pop. You can choose the coverage too, it’s buildable. So if you picked a too intense color like wicked apple, you can put it on your finger and dab over your lips and it will look super natural but more flustered. 10/10 product

Revlon usually does good lip colors. Maybelline color tattoo eyeshadow has a bunch of nice eyeshadow colors. Once you figure out what application technique works best for you, the eyeshadow really pays off. And it does last all day heck, even into the next day. When you apply it, keep your eye closed for about 30 seconds or so, that way the shadow will set and not crease when you open and close your eyes. Shadow doesn't even need touch ups.💯

transcript_raw.text: [Music]
Hi everyone! I'm going to show you how to achieve

this wet and glassy makeup 
look. Let's get started!

First things first, always wear sunscreen. 
This one from Etude House is my holy grail.
I’m trying this e.l.f. Luminous Putty Primer to

give my skin a subtle glow. 
So far, I really like it.
Of course, I’m using my under eye corrector from

Becca. This stuff works so well 
at correcting my dark circles.

For this look, I want to let my skin shine, 
so I’m concealing very intentionally,

only placing dots where I need them the most. 
And I make sure to blend it out really well.

And you know I had to double it. Of 
course concealing twice because I'm tired!
This is my go-to cushion foundation. It gives

my skin such a beautiful dewy 
finish and is so easy to apply.

To keep this look glowy, I’m only setting 
under my eyes and on my T-zone. Then I’m

taking a brush and just doing a very 
light dusting on the rest of my face.
For eyes, I’m using my Naked3 palette and taking

the shade “Limit” to apply a 
wash of color on my eyelids.

With the shade “Nooner,” I’m depositing it 
right in the outer corner and blending it

out with a fluffy brush. I’m also taking that 
same color on my lower eyelid for more depth.

I’m going in with this Stila Liquid 
Eyeshadow on the inner and center

parts of my eye and blending it 
with my finger. And I apply a

little bit at a time because I know 
I can always add more if I need to.
Now it’s time for the big guns. I’m using this

glitter liquid eyeshadow to give my 
eyes that jelly, glass-like effect.

For eyeliner, I’m using this brown liner and doing 
a very small wing, starting with the tail and

then drawing only up to the halfway point of my 
lash line. This keeps my eyes looking more open.

I’ve always been a Doe Lashes girl. 
I’ve had this pair for so long because

I prefer the 1.0 design. I really wish 
Doe still made their lashes like this.

I’m going to take that same brown 
liner and fill in the gap between

the band and my inner corner just so 
that there’s not an empty space there.
I love the tiny wand on this mascara because it’s

great for doing my bottom lashes, 
which are literally nonexistent.

I’m using this clear brow gel from Benefit and 
applying it to my brows to give them that “wet”

look. Then I’m just filling them in very lightly 
because I want to keep them looking natural.

I just bought this cream blush from 
Fenty and I’m already in love with it.

This is the shade “Strawberry Drip” 
and it compliments my skin so well.

For highlighter, I’m using this silvery 
one from ColourPop and applying it

generously to my cheek bones. I’m 
also going to put it on my nose,

brow bones, and cupid’s bow. It gives such 
a beautiful glow without looking too harsh.

This clear gloss from Fenty is called 
“Glass Slipper” and, hence the name,
is going to make my lips like glass.
Using this gloss from rom&nd,

I’m applying in the center of my lips. 
It really gives them that jelly effect.

Surprise! I’m using a different 
setting spray this time. This
one will give me that gorgeous, subtle, dewy look.

And we’re done! So pretty 
and wearable for every day!

Thank you guys for watching. Let me know 
what other makeup looks you want me to try.
Bye!
[Music]

Girl the orange lip oil and the red eyeshadow looked SO GOOD and also the haus labs blush? You deadass looked like a pinterest girlie

I'm not at all a huge make up wearer, but I absolutely love these videos and the lovely reviewer!! Very soothing while doing my skincare routine hi hi❤❤❤

Those cherry pick lip from About-face are SOOO freaking good. Find a natural color that is close to your lip color and it will just pop. You can choose the coverage too, it’s buildable. So if you picked a too intense color like wicked apple, you can put it on your finger and dab over your lips and it will look super natural but more flustered. 10/10 product

Revlon usually does good lip colors. Maybelline color tattoo eyeshadow has a bunch of nice eyeshadow colors. Once you figure out what application technique works best for you, the eyeshadow really pays off. And it does last all day heck, even into the next day. When you apply it, keep your eye closed for about 30 seconds or so, that way the shadow will set and not crease when you open and close your eyes. Shadow doesn't even need touch ups.💯
I usually poo poo the drugstore stuff but I'm so glad you're reviewing it because you really opened my eyes to new products, a big thank you to you!

Those cherry pick lip from About-face are SOOO freaking good. Find a natural color that is close to your lip color and it will just pop. You can choose the coverage too, it’s buildable. Once you figure out what application technique works best for you, the eyeshadow really pays off. And it does last all day heck, even into the next day. When you apply it, keep your eye closed for about 30 seconds or so, that way the shadow will set and not crease when you open and close your eyes. Shadow doesn't even need touch ups.💯

Nico - I'd love to get an update, maybe every few months, of what products you test that go into your daily rotation. There's definitely a big difference between "I liked this once" and "I like this so much I now use it every day."
That red eyeshadow looked so gorgeous on you and I love how you applied it!
Girl the orange lip oil and the red eyeshadow looked SO GOOD and also the haus labs blush? You deadass looked like a pinterest girlie
I love these so much! I look forward to them every month. Would you do a personal recommendations video of all of your favorite products, please?
OMG!! That red eyeshadow look! Have heard nothing but great things about Oden's Eye.  Awesome wrap up as usual. Ur the best reviewer. 🎉🎉
That HalfMagic blush looks so good. There’s a couple items I think I’m gonna try. Thank for another great video💖

So happy Oden's Eye is getting talked about more!! Their eyeshadow palettes are amazing, so much pigment and blend super well, and I have a few of their highlighters which I also love. Can't wait to try some of their singles too!
Watching Nico apply lipstick is like... hypnotic 💋 Man is she is stunning!!
I'm not at all a huge make up wearer, but I absolutely love these videos and the lovely reviewer!! Very soothing while doing my skincare routine hi hi❤❤❤

Those cherry pick lip from About-face are SOOO freaking good. Find a natural color that is close to your lip color and it will just pop. You can choose the coverage too, it’s buildable. So if you picked a too intense color like wicked apple, you can put it on your finger and dab over your lips and it will look super natural but more flustered. 10/10 product

Revlon usually does good lip colors. Maybelline color tattoo eyeshadow has a bunch of nice eyeshadow colors. Once you figure out what application technique works best for you, the eyeshadow really pays off. And it does last all day heck, even into the next day. When you apply it, keep your eye closed for about 30 seconds or so, that way the shadow will set and not crease when you open and close your eyes. Shadow doesn't even need touch ups.💯
I usually poo poo the drugstore stuff but I'm so glad you're reviewing it because you really opened my eyes to new products, a big thank you to you!

first_page_comments_list.comment: Red eyeshadow looks so good on you!!!

Nico - I'd love to get an update, maybe every few months, of what products you test that go into your daily rotation. There's definitely a big difference between "I liked this once" and "I like this so much I now use it every day."
That red eyeshadow looked so gorgeous on you and I love how you applied it!
Girl the orange lip oil and the red eyeshadow looked SO GOOD and also the haus labs blush? You deadass looked like a pinterest girlie
I love these so much! I look forward to them every month. Would you do a personal recommendations video of all of your favorite products, please?
OMG!! That red eyeshadow look! Have heard nothing but great things about Oden's Eye.  Awesome wrap up as usual. Ur the best reviewer. 🎉🎉
That HalfMagic blush looks so good. There’s a couple items I think I’m gonna try. Thank for another great video💖

So happy Oden's Eye is getting talked about more!! Their eyeshadow palettes are amazing, so much pigment and blend super well, and I have a few of their highlighters which I also love. Can't wait to try some of their singles too!
Watching Nico apply lipstick is like... hypnotic 💋 Man is she is stunning!!
I'm not at all a huge make up wearer, but I absolutely love these videos and the lovely reviewer!! Very soothing while doing my skincare routine hi hi❤❤❤

Those cherry pick lip from About-face are SOOO freaking good. Find a natural color that is close to your lip color and it will just pop. You can choose the coverage too, it’s buildable. So if you picked a too intense color like wicked apple, you can put it on your finger and dab over your lips and it will look super natural but more flustered. 10/10 product

Revlon usually does good lip colors. Maybelline color tattoo eyeshadow has a bunch of nice eyeshadow colors. Once you figure out what application technique works best for you, the eyeshadow really pays off. And it does last all day heck, even into the next day. Was ist von diesen Produkten zu halten, selbst wenn man sie ganz gut verträgt, schadet die Irritation der Haut evtl. Auf lange Sicht? Spam over.

Today I am going to show you different types of lipstick that make you look younger. **5 Tips That Will Make You LOOK YOUNGER After 60! https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KPIj9lB7tOA

Do you want to look 10 years younger naturally? This mature aging lip application for women in their 50s, 60s, or 70s will make you feel GLAMOROUS in no time.

Discover lipstick colors that will make you look younger than your age in this mature lips tutorial featuring aging lips. This will help you select your perfect lip look to feel fabulous during this beautiful phase of your life!

Lipsticks used in Video:
1. Balm: L'Oreal Glow Paradise in 110 Pastel Exaltation
2. Matte: L'Oreal Matte-Moiselle Pink in 703
3. Cream: L'Oreal Color Riche in Fairest Nude 800
4. Gloss: L'Oreal Gloss in 40 Blissful Blush 
5. LongWear: L'Oreal Longwear Lipstick in 111 Passionate Petal 

**Some of these (Cream, Matte and Balm) were paired the L'Oreal Color Riche lipliner in Beyond Pink.

Find me on instagram: @glamgirlgabi
Email me here: glamgirlgabibeauty@gmail.com
